# %60<..< -- Limits prompt to 60 chars

# %F{12}: Sets the text color to a specific color (12 usually corresponds to a shade of red, but it depends on the terminal's color settings).
# %f: Resets the text color to the default.
# %b: Resets any bold formatting (if applied).
# %k: Resets the color to the default foreground color.

